Pour the water for the rice (@Water for the Rice{300%ml}) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @Cornflour{10%g} into a #large bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{1%pack} to the bowl and toss to coat completely in the cornflour.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the chicken and fry until golden brown on the outside, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn every 2-3 mins.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Sambal Paste{15%g}, @Hoisin Sauce{64%g}, @Honey{15%g} and the @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

> Add less sambal paste if you'd prefer things milder.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for about 1 min.

Once the chicken is browned, transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the sliced pepper and green beans. Stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds} more.

Add your chicken back into the veg pan and pour in your sticky sauce, then bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium, then simmer until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add a splash of @?water{} to loosen the sauce if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When ready, fluff up the rice using a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with your sambal-hoisin chicken and veg, spooning over all the sauce from the pan.

Enjoy!